    <h1> Spaghetti Carbonara</h1>
    <img src="https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/6UaBC03j_WXNoBfyOgW2hDMec2g=/0x512/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():format(webp)/245775-spaghetti-alla-carbonara-the-traditional-italian-recipe-DDMFS-4x3-879c32ee3cfb463582e3e6230e311029.jpg" alt="Spaghetti carbonara">
    <h2> How to make it in less than 20 min!</h2>
    
    <p>This is an best meal I could to make in my teenage years</p>
    <p> Easy to make and good to eat !</p>


    <h3> Spaghetti alla Carbonara Ingredients</h3>

    <p> Here are all the simple ingredients youll need to make homemade pasta
        as if you were an italian </p>
    <ul>
        <li> <strong>Oil:</strong> </li>
        <li> <strong> guanciale </strong> </li>
        <li> <strong> spaghetti</strong> </li> 
        <li> <strong> eggs</strong> </li>
        <li><strong> Cheese</strong>  </li>
        <li> <strong> Extra Seasoning</strong> </li>
    </ul>

<h3> <Strong> <em> Steps</em></Strong></h3>

    <ol>
        <li> <strong>1.</strong>Cook the halal meat in olive oil until browned and crispy, then drain on paper towels.</li>
        <li> <strong>2.</strong> Boil the spaghetti in salted water. Drain and return to the pot. Let cool.</li>
        <li> <strong>3.</strong> Whisk the eggs, 1/2 of the cheese, and some pepper in a bowl until smooth.</li>
        <li> <strong>4.</strong>Pour the egg mixture over the pasta, stirring quickly, until creamy. </li>
        <li> <strong>5.</strong> Stir in the halal meat, then top with the remaining cheese and more black pepper.</li>

    </ol>

